{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> πτήσσω</b> <br /> (never πτήττω), [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Vespae” 1490, 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Institutio Cyri (Cyropaedia)” 3.3.18 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: <i>future</i> πτήξω [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “Anthologia Graeca” 12.141 codices (1st c.BC: Meleager Epigrammaticus)\">Refs 1st c.BC+</a>]: <i>aorist</i> ἔπτηξα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Hercules Furens” 974, etc.\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>], <i>Doric dialect</i> ἔπταξα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “P.” 4.57 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>], <i>Epic dialect</i> πτῆξα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 14.40: \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]<i>aorist 2</i> ἔπτᾰκον in <i>compound</i> καταπτακών [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Eumenides” 252 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; <i>Epic dialect</i> <i>3rd.pers.</i> <i>dual</i> καταπτήτην [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 8.136 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]: <i>perfect</i> ἔπτηχα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Isocrates Orator 5.58, (κατ-) 4th c.BC: Lycurgus Orator 40, 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 4.8 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; later ἔπτηκα (κατ-) [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.AD: Themistius Sophista “Orationes” 24.309b \">Refs 4th c.AD+</a>]; <i>Epic dialect</i> <i>participle</i> πεπτηώς, ῶτος (see.below[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 11.2). \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__I</b></Level2> Causal, <b>scare, alarm</b>, πτῆξε θυμὸν ἐνὶ στήθεσσιν Ἀχαιῶν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 14.40; ἐχθροὺς πτῆξαι 6th c.BC: Theognis Elegiacus 1015. \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <i>intransitive</i>, <b>crouch</b> or <b>cower for fear</b>, of animals, ἅπερ πτηνῶν ἀγέλαι τάχ᾽ ἂν σιγῇ