 175 (_anapaest meter_); φοβούμενοι πτήσσομεν αὐτούς 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Institutio Cyri (Cyropaedia)” 3.3.18; ταῖς διανοίαις μὴ πτήξαντες τὸν τῶν ἐπιόντων φόβον 4th c.BC: Lycurgus Orator 49; δόρυ 3rd c.BC: Lycophron Tragicus 280, “IG” 14.1296: _absolutely_, ὁ λέων.. ὁρώμενος.. οὐδέποτε φεύγει οὐδὲ πτήσσει 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Historia Animalium” 629b13. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]","strongNumber":"G8979","accentedUnicode":"πτήσσω","shortDef":"to alarm","mediumDef":"to alarm","stepGloss":"to alarm","stepTransliteration":"ptēssō","count":0,"_step_Type":"verb"}]}